  "prompt": "How long does it take for a natural tan to take hold after tanning in the sun?",
  "response": "A natural tan typically develops over a few hours to a few days after sun exposure:\n\n1. Initial color change: Within 1-2 hours after sun exposure, you might start to see some initial reddening or color change.\n\n2. Full tan development: The full tan usually takes 24-72 hours (1-3 days) to completely develop and darken.\n\n3. Peak color: The tan reaches its peak color about 48-72 hours after initial sun exposure.\n\nFactors that can affect tan development include:\n- Skin type\n- Intensity of sun exposure\n- Duration of sun exposure\n- Individual melanin production\n\nIt's important to note that tanning is actually a sign of skin damage, and prolonged sun exposure without proper protection can increase the risk of skin cancer and premature aging. Always use sunscreen and practice safe sun exposure.",
